    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Biographical Information </head>
      <p>Trio Beauty Salon opened on July 15, 1941 at 14 Newman Ave, Harrisonburg, VA. It was known
        formerly as the Gay Lynn Beauty Shop. The three partners of the Trio Beauty Salon were Flora
        Evelyn Taylor, Mildred Bridges, and Ava Gowl, but also included Ruby Dove and Beulah Ruth
        Kerns as owners and operators. Beulah Ruth Kerns married and became Beulah Ruth Kerns
        Clatterbuck and Flora Evelyn Taylor married and became Flora Evelyn Lamb and both names are
        reflected in the records. The salon was opened for 35 years before closing in 1976. After
        closing the salon, the owners continued to work elsewhere in the Harrisonburg area, and kept
        records of where they went. </p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content </head>
      <p>The Trio Beauty Salon Collection consists of various documents and records pertaining to
        the Trio Beauty Salon and its owners and operators, including business, financial and
        personal documents. The collection consists of business records, leases and agreements, tax
        and financial documents, and personal records of Beulah Ruth Kerns.</p>
    </scopecontent>

